A three-day State-level writers' conference will be organised under the aegis of the Prakasam District Writersâ€™ Association at the TTD Kalyanamandapam here from January 8.Deputy Speaker Mandali Buddha Prasad will inaugurate the conference which will bring together over 600 Telugu litterateurs from six States, including Sahitya Akademi Awardee K. Siva Reddy and Prof. Kolakaluri Enoch, former Vice Chancellor of Sri Venkateswara University, according to association president B. Hanuma Reddy.A galaxy of politicians including State Transport Minister Sidda Raghava Rao and YSR Congress whip in Parliament Y.V. Subba Reddy will grace the occasion.Ghazal Srinivas will enthral the audience with his Telugu Ghazals.